<br>
Question: How do I go further in the Blades? I see that apparently I still can go higher, but for some reason I have no idea who I go to see about actually raising ranks. Did I screw myself after Cassius left from going any higher?<br>
<br>
As far as buying the expansion is concerned, I'm going to hold back and wait for others to get it because if it still kicks folks out of the game as often as it does right now, I'd rather not buy another crash-ridden product. Bad enough I have to use Windows. Wonder if they will bring the expansion out on my Xbox? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/urabican1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rabican1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/26/02 1:25:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=117.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Expansion for Morrowind</span><hr size=1> Phixer,<br>
<br>
Head to <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.elderscrolls.com/ubbthreads/ubbthreads.php">www.elderscrolls.com/ubbt...hreads.php</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> the folks at that board may be able to answer your quest questions.<br>
<br>
I really haven't been able to do any marathon sessions and as a result haven't done to many of the quest chains. So far I have released &quot;Milo&quot; from captivity in Vivec. I have also done a bunch of “errands” for the mage, fighter and thief guilds. I also slaughtered all the guys at the Corner Club in Balmora.  I thought about trying to taunt each NPC into attacking me, but hack and slash was more fun. Also I have found killing Ordinators in Vivec to be profitable. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So far I really enjoy Morrowind. There are a ton of quests to do or not, if you choose. I have also find the combat very interactive. I like being able to actually use position and obstacles in combat to my advantage.<br>
